    "created_at": "2014-02-11T04:48:45Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-02-11T04:48:45Z",
    "body": "I'm doing a build right now that restores the old logic of\n\n``` rust\n            let dirpath = match *odir {\n                Some(ref d) => d.clone(),\n                None => match *input {\n                    StrInput(_) => os::getcwd(),\n                    FileInput(ref ifile) => ifile.dir_path()\n                }\n            };\n```\n\nThat said, I think I like `Path::new(\".\")` better, because that matches my expectation of `--out-dir` defaulting to `.`.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
